title: ModelRepository
description: A description of a model repository for HTR/OCR

project-name.description: Name of the project (If different from the dataset name)

language.description: Language present in the dataset (Using ISO-639 codes)

script.description: Script of the ground truth (Using ISO-15924)

iso.description: ISO value refering to a script

qualify.description: Free text to qualify the script if the ISO value is not enough

source.description: Mode of production of the source data

time.description: Period covered by the training data used to create the model

notBefore.description: Date before which the dataset has no data (YYYY-MM-DD)

notAfter.description: Date after which the dataset has no data (YYYY-MM-DD)

hands.description: Details about the number of fonts or hands in the dataset

count.description: Number of hands/fonts present in the dataset

precision.description: Level of precision of the count property

volume.description: Details about the quantity of training data

source.description: Mode of production of the source data

type.description: Defines the function(s) of the model

name.description: Name of the contributor, full-name for institutions

surname.description: For people, surname of the contributor

software.description: Identifier(s) of the software(s) this model can be used with.

sources.description: Sources that are present in the dataset

link.description: URL of the resource or a link to its catalog page for example

description.description: Free text field to describe the source

transcription-guidelines.description: Guidelines used to transcribe the resources (normalization, resolution of abbreviation, correction of mispelling, etc.)

license.description: Licence under which the data are shared

name.description: Name of the Licence, eg. CC-BY 4.0

characters.description: Information about the character set of the model (if applicable)

transliteration.description: Whether ASCII or other kind of characters are used to represent other glyphs, such as Betacode or Hieroglyphic transliteration.
